What are containers, 
If we use containers then for each microservice Accounts, Loans, Cards. We can have different types of JDK version for loans we can have different Java 8 for cards we can have Java 10 and Spring Boot Libraries. 

Container Engine is Docker. 

A container is a loosely isolated environment that allows us to build and run software packages, These software packages include the code and all the dependencies to run the application quickly and reliably on any computing environment. we call these packages as docker images

A container is a lightweight, isolated runtime environment that packages:

Application code

Runtime (Java, Python, Node, etc.)

Libraries

Dependencies

System tools

Everything needed to run the application consistently anywhere.

Containerization:
Containerization is the process/technology of packaging applications into containers.
So containerization = method of creating and running containers.
Spring Boot App
      ↓
Docker Image
      ↓
Run Container
      ↓
Application Running

Docker is the most popular platform/tool used to implement containerization.

It provides everything needed to:

Build container images

Run containers

Manage containers

Distribute containers

